Ficha 4

1.
a) 
i. 12KiB -> 20KiB, 10KiB -> 10KiB, 9KiB -> 18KiB.  (Primeiro lugar com espaço)
ii. 12KiB -> 20KiB, 10KiB -> 18KiB, 9KiB -> 9KiB. (Começa com first fit, e dps segue de onde estava não volta ao início)
iii. 12KiB -> 12KiB, 10KiB -> 10KiB, 9KiB -> 9KiB. (Escolha do melhor espaço de alocação)
iv. 12KiB -> 20KiB, 10KiB -> 18KiB, 9KiB-> 15KiB. (Escolha do maior espaço para alocação).

b)
best fit >> next fit >> first fit >> worst fit.

2.
Advantage -> Swapping in and out a few pages is less expensive operation than swapping in and out the whole process at one go.
Disadvantage -> Longer memory lookup times compared to variable memory, page tables consume additional memory.

3.
Using the mapping of page 0, it will reach a point when there are a lot of processes running and there will need to be an overlap of memory, because the allocated memory of each process are on top of one another.

11.
Slide 27 Memory Management.
b) No because in both cases the total address space can exceed the sizo of physical memory.

